<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-brand-neutral">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold text-center text-primary mb-12">
      Financial Myths Debunked: Clarity You Can Trust.
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-4">
      <!-- Accordion Item 1 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-slate-200 py-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
          <span class="font-serif text-xl text-primary">Is my spouse's 401(k) automatically mine?</span>
          <span class="transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
          <p>Not necessarily. While spouses often have rights to retirement assets accumulated during a marriage, ownership can be complex, especially in cases of divorce or prenuptial agreements. State laws vary significantly. It's a common misconception that can lead to major surprises during life transitions.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Accordion Item 2 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-slate-200 py-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
          <span class="font-serif text-xl text-primary">If I have a Will, is my Estate Planning done?</span>
          <span class="transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
          <p>A will is a crucial first step, but it is not a complete estate plan. A comprehensive plan also addresses things like healthcare directives, power of attorney, and strategies to minimize estate taxes and probate. Trusts, for example, can offer control and privacy that a simple will cannot.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Accordion Item 3 -->
      <details class="group border-b border-slate-200 py-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
          <span class="font-serif text-xl text-primary">Do I need a planner if I use TurboTax?</span>
          <span class="transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
          <p>Tax software is excellent for tax compliance (filing), but it doesn't provide tax strategy (planning). A financial planner helps you make decisions today that will legally and ethically minimize your tax burden in the future, looking at the entire picture of your investments, income, and goals.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Add more accordion items as needed -->
       <details class="group border-b border-slate-200 py-4">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer list-none">
          <span class="font-serif text-xl text-primary">Is all debt "bad" debt?</span>
          <span class="transform group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
          <p>No. It's crucial to distinguish between high-interest, non-productive debt (like credit card debt) and strategic, low-interest debt used to acquire appreciating assets (like a mortgage on a home or a loan for a business). Managing this difference is key to building wealth.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* This hides the default marker from the <summary> tag */
  summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }
</style>
